<!--
  Notification icon for in-call foreground-service.

  Android requires notification icons to be single-color silhouettes
  (the system tints them at runtime; full-color icons fail Android 8+
  rendering rules and produce a blank tile). The launcher mipmap
  `ic_launcher` is full-color and unsuitable — react-native-callkeep
  also looks in `R.drawable.*` only, not mipmap, so passing
  `ic_launcher` from the bridge errored out at foreground-service
  start time and crashed the app at enrollment-completion (the
  alpha-0.4.20 reproducer that motivated deferring CallKeep init).

  This is a 24dp phone glyph, white-on-transparent. Android tints it
  to whatever the active notification theme calls for.
-->
